9. But this he frequently does, even when we do not give way to any positive sin. It is enough, it gives him sufficient advantage, if we do not ‘stir up the gift of God which is in us’;
Cf. 2 Tim. 1:6. if we do not ‘agonize’ continually ‘to enter in at the strait gate’;
Luke 13:24 (Notes). if we do not earnestly ‘strive for the mastery’,
Cf. 2 Tim. 2:5. and ‘take the kingdom of heaven by violence’.
Cf. Matt. 11:12 (Notes). There needs no more than not to fight, and we are sure to be conquered. Let us only be careless or ‘faint in our mind’,
Cf. Heb. 12:3. let us be easy and indolent, and our natural darkness will soon return, and overspread our soul. It is enough, therefore, if we give way to spiritual sloth: this will effectually darken the soul. It will as surely destroy the light of God, if not so swiftly, as murder or adultery.
